paragraphs.title: Fetch 90 day logs - split into Failed Events and Regular Events - Create Daily Summary per hour
paragraphs.text:
%spark2
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._

val path = "/tmp/rsyslogs/*.txt"
val df = spark.read.option("header", "false").csv(path)


val rsysDF = df.select(
    from_unixtime(df("_c0")).as("ts")
    ,df("_c1").cast(StringType).as("sessionid")
    ,df("_c2").cast(StringType).as("hostname")
    ,df("_c3").cast(StringType).as("service")
    ,df("_c4").cast(StringType).as("username")
    ,df("_c5").cast(StringType).as("event")    
    )
val rsysDF90day = rsysDF.filter(rsysDF("ts").gt(date_sub(current_date(),341)))  // Fetch last 13 months
    
rsysDF90day.createOrReplaceTempView("rsyslog")

val interimDF = spark.sql("select to_date(ts) as date,  date_format(ts, 'M') as Month, date_format(ts, 'u') as DayOfWeek, date_format(ts, 'd') as Day, date_format(ts, 'H') as Hour, cast(date_format(ts, 'm') as double) as minute, hostname, service, username, case when event ='failure' then 1 else 0 end as Failure, case when event ='opened' then 1 else 0 end as Opened, case when event ='closed' then 1 else 0 end as Closed from rsyslog")

// Quantile Discretizer to convert into 12 Bins ( 60min into 5 minute bins)
import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.QuantileDiscretizer

val discretizer = new QuantileDiscretizer()
  .setInputCol("minute")
  .setOutputCol("bin")
  .setNumBuckets(12)
  
val discretizerDF = discretizer.fit(interimDF).transform(interimDF)
discretizerDF.createOrReplaceTempView("5minBins")

val DailySummDF = spark.sql("select date, month, DayOfWeek, Day, Hour, Bin, hostname, service, username, Sum(Failure) as NoOfFailures, Sum(Opened) as NoOfOpened, Sum(Closed) as NoOfClosed from 5minBins group by date, month, DayOfWeek, Day, Hour, Bin, hostname, service, username")
//DailySummDF.cache()

DailySummDF.createOrReplaceTempView("dailySumm")

val hourlySummDF = spark.sql("select cast(month as int), cast(DayOfWeek as int), cast(day as int),  cast(hour as int), hostname, service, username, Avg(NoOfFailures) AvgFailures,  Avg(NoOfOpened) AvgOpened,  Avg(NoOfClosed) AvgClosed  from dailySumm group by month, DayOfWeek, day, hour, hostname, service, username")
hourlySummDF.cache()
hourlySummDF.createOrReplaceTempView("hourlySumm")
//hourlySummDF.show()

paragraphs.title: Regression Model - Failures
paragraphs.text:
%spark2

import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.{OneHotEncoder, StringIndexer}
import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.VectorAssembler
import org.apache.spark.ml.regression.{ GeneralizedLinearRegression, GeneralizedLinearRegressionModel,GeneralizedLinearRegressionSummary}
import org.apache.spark.ml.Pipeline

 
val usernameIdx = new StringIndexer().setInputCol("username").setOutputCol("usernameIdx")
val usernameEncoder = new OneHotEncoder().setInputCol("usernameIdx").setOutputCol("usernameVec")

val serviceIdx = new StringIndexer().setInputCol("service").setOutputCol("serviceIdx")
val serviceEncorder = new OneHotEncoder().setInputCol("serviceIdx").setOutputCol("serviceVec")

val hostnameIdx = new StringIndexer().setInputCol("hostname").setOutputCol("hostnameIdx")
val hostnameEncoder = new OneHotEncoder().setInputCol("hostnameIdx").setOutputCol("hostnameVec")

val input = hourlySummDF
val sets = input.randomSplit(Array[Double](0.9, 0.1), 18)
val training = sets(0)
val test = sets(1)


val assembler = new VectorAssembler().setInputCols(Array("month", "DayOfWeek", "day", "hour", "usernameVec", "serviceVec", "hostnameVec","AvgFailures" )).setOutputCol("features")

//=== GLR ====
val glr = new GeneralizedLinearRegression()
  .setFamily("gaussian")
  .setLink("identity")
  .setFeaturesCol("features")
  .setLabelCol("AvgFailures")
  .setPredictionCol("prediction")
  .setMaxIter(100)
  .setRegParam(0.3)


val pipeline = new Pipeline().setStages(Array( usernameIdx, usernameEncoder, serviceIdx, serviceEncorder,  hostnameIdx, hostnameEncoder, assembler, glr))

val PredictionModel = pipeline.fit(input)

val pipelineModel = PredictionModel.stages(7).asInstanceOf[GeneralizedLinearRegressionModel]


    // Save the PMML  model
    import org.jpmml.sparkml._
    import org.jpmml.model._
    import javax.xml.transform.stream.StreamResult
    import java.io.StringWriter;
    import java.util.Date;
    import java.text.SimpleDateFormat;

    val fileName = new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MMM-dd_HH_mm_ss'-GLRModel-Failures'").format(new Date());
    val destLocation = fileName.toString()

    val pmml = ConverterUtil.toPMML(input.schema, PredictionModel)

    val outWriter = new StringWriter()
    val result = new StreamResult(outWriter)
    JAXBUtil.marshalPMML(pmml, (result))

    // === WRITE PMML to HDFS
    import org.apache.hadoop.conf.Configuration
    import org.apache.hadoop.fs._

    val hadoopConfig: Configuration = sc.hadoopConfiguration
    val fs: FileSystem = org.apache.hadoop.fs.FileSystem.get(hadoopConfig)
    val path = new Path(  "/tmp/PMML/" + destLocation);
    val os = fs.create(path)
    os.write(outWriter.toString.getBytes)
    fs.close()
    
    //System.setProperty("HADOOP_USER_NAME", "zeppelin")
    

// Print the coefficients and intercept for generalized linear regression model
println(s"Coefficients: ${pipelineModel.coefficients}")

// Summarize the model over the training set and print out some metrics
val summary = pipelineModel.summary
println(s"Coefficient Standard Errors: ${summary.coefficientStandardErrors.mkString(",")}")
println(s"T Values: ${summary.tValues.mkString(",")}")
println(s"P Values: ${summary.pValues.mkString(",")}")
println(s"Dispersion: ${summary.dispersion}")
println(s"Null Deviance: ${summary.nullDeviance}")
println(s"Residual Degree Of Freedom Null: ${summary.residualDegreeOfFreedomNull}")
println(s"Deviance: ${summary.deviance}")
println(s"Residual Degree Of Freedom: ${summary.residualDegreeOfFreedom}")

import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.{OneHotEncoder, StringIndexer}

import org.apache.spark.ml.Pipeline

 
val usernameIdx = new StringIndexer().setInputCol("username").setOutputCol("usernameIdx")
val usernameEncoder = new OneHotEncoder().setInputCol("usernameIdx").setOutputCol("usernameVec")

val serviceIdx = new StringIndexer().setInputCol("service").setOutputCol("serviceIdx")
val serviceEncorder = new OneHotEncoder().setInputCol("serviceIdx").setOutputCol("serviceVec")

val hostnameIdx = new StringIndexer().setInputCol("hostname").setOutputCol("hostnameIdx")
val hostnameEncoder = new OneHotEncoder().setInputCol("hostnameIdx").setOutputCol("hostnameVec")

val input = hourlySummDF
val sets = input.randomSplit(Array[Double](0.9, 0.1), 18)
val training = sets(0)
val test = sets(1)

//=== GLR ====
val glr = new GeneralizedLinearRegression()
  .setFamily("gaussian")
  .setLink("identity")
  .setFeaturesCol("features")
  .setLabelCol("AvgOpened")
  .setPredictionCol("prediction")
  .setMaxIter(100)
  .setRegParam(0.3)


val pipeline = new Pipeline().setStages(Array( usernameIdx, usernameEncoder, serviceIdx, serviceEncorder,  hostnameIdx, hostnameEncoder, assembler, glr))
